# UI Improvement Guidelines

## Current State
The app has a functional skeleton with correct content and behavior. Focus on enhancing the visual presentation and user experience without changing the underlying logic or content.

## Key Files
- Main quiz interface: [app/page.tsx](mdc:app/page.tsx)
- Results pages: [app/results/](mdc:app/results/)
- Global styles: [app/globals.css](mdc:app/globals.css)
- Quiz data: [app/quiz-data.ts](mdc:app/quiz-data.ts)

## UI Enhancement Priorities

### 1. Visual Polish
- Improve card designs with better shadows, gradients, and borders
- Enhance button hover states and transitions
- Add micro-animations for better feedback
- Improve typography hierarchy and spacing

### 2. Interactive Elements
- Better choice button designs with clear visual feedback
- Improved progress indicators
- Enhanced loading states
- Smoother transitions between quiz phases

### 3. Results Display
- More engaging results presentation
- Better visual hierarchy for movement patterns
- Improved archetype showcase
- Enhanced pattern insights display

### 4. Responsive Design
- Ensure all components work well on mobile
- Optimize touch interactions
- Improve spacing for different screen sizes

## Design System
- **Colors**: Use existing CSS variables (--gold, --cobalt, --plum, etc.)
- **Typography**: Maintain Inter font family
- **Spacing**: Use consistent padding/margin patterns
- **Animations**: Keep smooth transitions with --dur and --ease variables

## Content Preservation
- **DO NOT** change quiz logic, scoring, or data processing
- **DO NOT** modify archetype definitions or movement descriptions
- **DO NOT** alter the results calculation algorithms
- **DO** focus purely on visual presentation and user experience

## Implementation Notes
- Use Tailwind CSS classes for rapid styling
- Leverage existing CSS custom properties
- Maintain accessibility standards
- Test on multiple screen sizes